& = \frac{6(\sqrt b + \sqrt c + \sqrt a)}{4abc}\\
&\geq \frac{3}{\sqrt{abc}}\left(\sqrt a + \sqrt b + \sqrt c\right).
\end{align*}
\]
So maximum value is $3$. <answer>

So let $x = \sqrt{a}$, etc., then we want the maximum value of $\frac{4x}{\sqrt{y^3z}} + \frac{6y}{\sqrt{xyz^3}} + \frac{12z}{\sqrt{x^3y^2}}$, where $x > 0$, $y > 0$, $z > 0$, and $(xz)^2 + (yz)^3 + (xy)^3 = 4.$</think><answer> Apply AM-GM to the numerator and use the given constraint to bound from above:
$\begin{align*}
\frac{4x}{\sqrt{y^3 z}} + \frac{6y}{\sqrt{xz^3}} + \frac{12 z}{\sqrt{x^3 y^2}}
&\leq \frac{4x}{2 \sqrt{z^3 y}} + \frac{6y}{\sqrt[3]{xz^4}} + \frac{12z}{\sqrt[3]{x^2 z^3}} \\
&= 2 \sqrt{y} + 3 \sqrt[3]{z} + 6 \sqrt{x}.
\end{align*}[Answer]</answer>

problem:
A solid right prism $ABCDEF$ has a height of 16, as shown. Also, its bases are equilateral triangles with side length 12. Points $X$, $Y$, and $Z$ are the midpoints of edges $AC$, $BC$, and $DC$, respectively. Determine the perimeter of triangle $XYZ$. [asy]
pair A, B, C, D, E, F, X, Y, Z;
A=(0,0);
B=(12,0);
C=(6,-6);
D=(6,-22);
E=(0,-16);
F=(12,-16);
X=(A+C)/2;
Y=(B+C)/2;
Z=(C+D)/2;
draw(A--B--C--A--E--D--F--B--C--D);
draw(X--Y--Z--X, dashed);
label("$A$", A, NW);
label("$B$", B, NE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$D$", D, S);
label("$E$", E, SW);
label("$F$", F, SE);
label("$X$", X, SW);
label("$Y$", Y, SE);
label("$Z$", Z, SE);
label("12", (A+B)/2, dir(90));
label("16", (B+F)/2, dir(0));
[/asy]

